From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xiaoyi He <xiaoyihe.ustc@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 18:00:58 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Add xs mod partition for M5StackChan CoreS3

The stock CoreS3 partition table has no type-0x40 xs partition, so mods
cannot install at all (xsHost.c mounts mods from the first 0x40/1
partition). Reserve 2MB at 0xDF0000 on the 16MB flash; the factory app
partition stays 0xDE0000. The layout leaves the final 64KB available for
the existing storage partition.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 firmware/platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/manifest.json      | 3 ++-
 .../platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/partitions-matchday.csv | 9 +++++++++
 2 files changed, 11 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 firmware/platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/partitions-matchday.csv

diff --git a/firmware/platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/manifest.json b/firmware/platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/manifest.json
index 318406e..faf55da 100644
--- a/firmware/platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/manifest.json
+++ b/firmware/platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/manifest.json
@@ -1,6 +1,7 @@
 {
   "build": {
-    "SUBPLATFORM": "m5stackchan_cores3"
+    "SUBPLATFORM": "m5stackchan_cores3",
+    "PARTITIONS_FILE": "./partitions-matchday.csv"
   },
   "include": [
     "$(BUILD)/devices/esp32/targets/m5stack_cores3/manifest.json",
diff --git a/firmware/platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/partitions-matchday.csv b/firmware/platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/partitions-matchday.csv
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..9ee530c
--- /dev/null
+++ b/firmware/platforms/m5stackchan_cores3/partitions-matchday.csv
@@ -0,0 +1,9 @@
+# M5StackChan CoreS3 (16MB flash) with a 2MB `xs` mod partition so user
+# applications install with `npm run mod` instead of reflashing the host.
+# The final 64KB remains available for the existing storage partition.
+# Name,   Type, SubType, Offset,  Size, Flags
+nvs,      data, nvs,     0x9000,   0x006000,
+phy_init, data, phy,     0xF000,   0x001000,
+factory,  app,  factory, 0x10000,  0xDE0000,
+xs,       0x40, 1,       0xDF0000, 0x200000,
+storage,  data, spiffs,  0xFF0000, 0x010000,
